---
title: BBQ Jackfruit Open Burgers (v) with Wedges and Salad
description: Jackfruit is a spiky fruit originating in Southern India which has a 'meaty' texture when cooked which is why many people use it to create plant-based versions of shredded chicken, pulled pork, or other meat-based recipes.  In this recipe, we've simmered young jackfruit in a smoky barbecue-style sauce until the texture is sticky and stringy. Divided between toasted burger buns, topped with cheese and served with a crunchy salad and chunky potato wedges, these jackfruit burgers are the ultimate vegetarian treat.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/bbq-jackfruit-open-burgers-84480d4d-efcae22d.jpg
